&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At ACT Commodities we trade environmental products and help our clients reach their environmental and sustainability objectives through trading products such as carbon offsets, environmental certificates, biofuels and many others. We do this by utilizing our knowledge and network. We are a young-minded company with 400+ ambitious people from all over the world, all working in an open environment where no day is the same.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated and analytical Business Commercial Intern to join our S&amp;amp;W team. This internship offers an exciting opportunity to support strategic initiatives by identifying and assessing environmental product trends and business opportunities across the Asia-Pacific (APAC) region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the team, you will gain practical exposure to a fast-growing and dynamic sector, supporting the trading team in the registration and onboarding of environmental assets and conducting targeted market research to guide commercial and regional decision-making. You’ll learn how environmental commodities are structured, tracked, and traded, while contributing insights that help strengthen the company’s market position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;fontstyle0&quot;&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the trading team in the end-to-end process of registering and onboarding environmental assets across various registries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate documentation and ensure compliance with registry requirements and internal controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct qualitative and quantitative market research on environmental commodities, regulatory developments, and emerging market opportunities in APAC.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in gathering, organizing, and analyzing data from public databases, industry reports, and proprietary sources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare concise market updates, asset summaries, and internal briefing materials for commercial and trading stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal stakeholders to support ad hoc market research.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;69&quot; data-end=&quot;77&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;69&quot; data-end=&quot;77&quot;&gt;公司介绍&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;79&quot; data-end=&quot;236&quot;&gt;在 ACT Commodities，我们从事环境产品交易，并通过交易碳抵消、环境证书、生物燃料等多种产品，帮助客户实现其环境与可持续发展目标。我们通过自身的专业知识和广泛的网络来实现这一点。公司拥有超过400名来自世界各地、充满抱负的员工，秉持年轻化的企业文化，在一个开放且充满活力的环境中工作，每一天都充满变化。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr data-start=&quot;238&quot; data-end=&quot;241&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;243&quot; data-end=&quot;251&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;243&quot; data-end=&quot;251&quot;&gt;岗位介绍&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;253&quot; data-end=&quot;375&quot;&gt;我们正在寻找一位积极主动、具备分析能力的商业实习生（Business Commercial Intern）加入我们的 S&amp;amp;W 团队。该实习机会将为您提供一个参与战略项目的良好平台，主要负责在亚太地区（APAC）识别和评估环境产品趋势及商业机会。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;377&quot; data-end=&quot;496&quot;&gt;作为团队的一员，您将有机会接触一个快速发展且充满活力的行业，支持交易团队完成环境资产的注册及上线流程，并开展有针对性的市场研究，为商业及区域决策提供支持。您将学习环境大宗商品的结构、追踪及交易方式，同时通过提供洞察来增强公司的市场竞争力。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr data-start=&quot;498&quot; data-end=&quot;501&quot;&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;503&quot; data-end=&quot;511&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;503&quot; data-end=&quot;511&quot;&gt;主要职责&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;513&quot; data-end=&quot;729&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;513&quot; data-end=&quot;550&quot;&gt;协助交易团队完成各类环境资产在不同注册机构中的全流程注册及上线工作&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;551&quot; data-end=&quot;585&quot;&gt;维护准确的文件记录，并确保符合注册机构要求及公司内部控制规范&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;586&quot; data-end=&quot;628&quot;&gt;针对亚太地区的环境大宗商品、政策法规发展及新兴市场机会开展定性与定量市场研究&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;629

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At ACT Commodities we trade environmental products and help our clients reach their environmental and sustainability objectives through trading products such as carbon offsets, environmental certificates, biofuels and many others. We do this by utilizing our knowledge and network. We are a young-minded company with 400+ ambitious people from all over the world, all working in an open environment where no day is the same.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated and analytical Business Commercial Intern to join our S&amp;amp;W team. This internship offers an exciting opportunity to support strategic initiatives by identifying and assessing environmental product trends and business opportunities across the Asia-Pacific (APAC) region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the team, you will gain practical exposure to a fast-growing and dynamic sector, supporting the trading team in the registration and onboarding of environmental assets and conducting targeted market research to guide commercial and regional decision-making. You’ll learn how environmental commodities are structured, tracked, and traded, while contributing insights that help strengthen the company’s market position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;fontstyle0&quot;&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the trading team in the end-to-end process of registering and onboarding environmental assets across various registries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate documentation and ensure compliance with registry requirements and internal controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct qualitative and quantitative market research on environmental commodities, regulatory developments, and emerging market opportunities in APAC.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in gathering, organizing, and analyzing data from public databases, industry reports, and proprietary sources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare concise market updates, asset summaries, and internal briefing materials for commercial and trading stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal stakeholders to support ad hoc market research.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tu Rol en Nuestra Historia&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;En esencia, su función implica:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;157&quot; data-end=&quot;260&quot;&gt;Impulsar la creación y expansión del negocio de CAEs de ACT en España, construyendo mercado desde cero.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;262&quot; data-end=&quot;366&quot;&gt;Identificar y desarrollar oportunidades reales de generación de CAEs en sectores industrial y terciario.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;368&quot; data-end=&quot;514&quot;&gt;Construir, gestionar y escalar un pipeline sólido de proyectos de Eficiencia Energética, desde la generación de leads hasta el cierre de acuerdos.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;516&quot; data-end=&quot;639&quot;&gt;Analizar la viabilidad técnica y económica de proyectos CAE en estrecha colaboración con los equipos técnicos y operativos.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;641&quot; data-end=&quot;788&quot;&gt;Contribuir activamente a la definición e implementación de la estrategia comercial de ACT Group para el mercado de Eficiencia Energética en España.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;790&quot; data-end=&quot;939&quot;&gt;Desarrollar y consolidar un ecosistema estratégico de partners: ingenierías, instaladores, ESCOs, agregadores, clientes finales y entidades públicas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;941&quot; data-end=&quot;1066&quot;&gt;Representar a ACT en eventos, asociaciones y foros del sector para posicionar a la compañía como referente en el mercado CAE.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1068&quot; data-end=&quot;1181&quot;&gt;Traducir la complejidad regulatoria en propuestas comerciales claras, estructuradas y atractivas para el cliente.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1183&quot; data-end=&quot;1360&quot;&gt;Colaborar de forma transversal con equipos internos (ventas, legal, operaciones y dirección) para garantizar una ejecución fluida de los proyectos y generar valor a largo plazo.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tu Experiencia:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para tener éxito en este puesto, buscamos candidatos con las siguientes calificaciones y atributos:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1485&quot; data-end=&quot;1591&quot;&gt;Al menos 3 años de experiencia en desarrollo de negocio, ventas consultivas o roles comerciales similares.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1593&quot; data-end=&quot;1711&quot;&gt;Formación universitaria en Ingeniería (energética, industrial, minas), Administración de Empresas, Economía o similar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1713&quot; data-end=&quot;1798&quot;&gt;Mentalidad emprendedora, con autonomía, iniciativa y fuerte orientación a resultados.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1800&quot; data-end=&quot;1911&quot;&gt;Capacidad para desenvolverse en un entorno en construcción, con procesos flexibles y alto ritmo de crecimiento.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1913&quot; data-end=&quot;1985&quot;&gt;Capacidad analítica combinada con visión comercial y curiosidad técnica.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1987&quot; data-end=&quot;2117&quot;&gt;Comodidad trabajando con marcos regulatorios y habilidad para explicar conceptos complejos de manera clara y orientada al cliente.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2119&quot; data-end=&quot;2176&quot;&gt;Disponibilidad para viajar regularmente dentro de España.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2178&quot; data-end=&quot;2218&quot;&gt;Dominio profesional de español e inglés.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2178&quot; data-end=&quot;2218&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;2220&quot; data-end=&quot;2259&quot;&gt;Será un plus si además cuentas con:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;2261&quot; data-end=&quot;2351&quot;&gt;Experiencia previa en el sector energético, eficiencia energética o servicios energéticos.

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role in Our Story:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;At ACT, we believe carbon markets are one of the most powerful tools for accelerating the global energy transition. As governments introduce new regulations, compliance programs, and market frameworks, businesses need trusted partners to help them navigate complexity and unlock opportunity. As a Carbon Markets Specialist, you will sit at the intersection of policy, markets, and innovation. You&#39;ll help ACT stay ahead of regulatory developments across North American and global carbon markets, translating complex policy changes into actionable insights that drive commercial strategy, product development, and market expansion. In essence, your role involves:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and analyze carbon market policies, regulations, and market developments across U.S., Canadian, and international programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex regulatory frameworks into clear, actionable insights for commercial, product, and leadership teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities for new products and services based on evolving market dynamics and regulatory changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with commercial, legal, and operations teams to ensure products are compliant, relevant, and ready for market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to ACT&#39;s thought leadership through market analysis, policy commentary, and external communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent ACT at industry conferences, workshops, and stakeholder engagements, building relationships with market participants and regulatory bodies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help shape ACT&#39;s strategic response to emerging trends in carbon and environmental markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Your expertise will directly influence how ACT supports clients through regulatory change, develops innovative market solutions, and expands into new opportunities. Working across teams and engaging with key stakeholders, you&#39;ll play a critical role in strengthening ACT&#39;s position as a trusted leader in environmental commodities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to make a tangible impact, helping businesses decarbonize, supporting the growth of carbon markets, and contributing to the solutions that will define the future of the energy transition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Expertise:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;0 0 []&quot;&gt;To be successful in this role, we are looking for candidates with the following qualification and attributes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-spread=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 - 6 years of experience in carbon markets, environmental commodities, energy markets, policy analysis, regulation, market research, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Bachelor&#39;s degree in Public Policy, Environmental Science, Economics, Business, Engineering, or a related discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills and the ability to interpret complex regulatory frameworks&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW4280703 BCX0&quot;&gt;; t&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;NormalTextRun SCXW4280703 BCX0&quot;&gt;he ability to connect policy insights to commercial opportunities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of key North American carbon programs, including the Western Climate Initiative (WCI), Alberta TIER, British Columbia OBPS, and New York Cap-and-Invest (NYCI).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with broader environmental markets and emerging policy mechanisms such as voluntary carbon markets (VCM), CORSIA, Article 6, tax credits, power, and fuels markets is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quantitative and analytical capabilities, including assessing commodity market fundamentals and uncovering emerging market opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic thinker skilled at synthesiz

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Votre rôle chez nous :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Au sein du bureau parisien, le/la Chargé(e) de Production CEE est responsable du chiffrage des opérations d’efficacité énergétique et de l’instruction des dossiers CEE des clients d’ACT dans les secteurs de l’Industrie, du Bâtiment, du Tertiaire, de l’Agriculture, de la Santé et du secteur public. Le/la Chargé(e) de Production CEE assure également le suivi des dossiers en relation avec les clients et les partenaires tout au long du processus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essentiellement, votre rôle consiste à :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Étude et Éligibilité des Projets CEE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Évaluer l&#39;éligibilité des projets CEE selon les critères définis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Estimer les gisements CEE pour différents projets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calculer les primes associées aux projets CEE pour les clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Montage et Suivi des Dossiers CEE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assurer le montage administratif des dossiers CEE.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Suivre les dossiers du portefeuille clients tout au long de leur cycle de vie.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Préparer et soumettre les dossiers aux organismes compétents pour validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Gestion de la Relation Client&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Être l&#39;interlocuteur/trice dédié(e) des clients durant le processus de montage du dossier CEE jusqu&#39;au dépôt.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conseiller les clients sur les meilleures pratiques et les accompagner dans la constitution de leurs dossiers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Développer une relation de confiance avec les clients et répondre à leurs besoins et préoccupations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaboration et Coordination avec les Partenaires&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travailler en étroite collaboration avec les partenaires et les installateurs de matériel éligible aux CEE.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Développer des partenariats nationaux pour optimiser le processus de montage des dossiers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordonner les interactions entre les différents acteurs du processus CEE.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Votre expertise :&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pour réussir dans cette fonction, nous recherchons des candidats possédant les qualifications et les qualités suivantes :&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diplôme universitaire dans un domaine pertinent (énergie, environnement, ingénierie) ou expérience professionnelle équivalente.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Expérience avérée dans la gestion de dossiers CEE ou dans un domaine connexe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connaissance approfondie des réglementations et des normes relatives aux CEE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Solides compétences en gestion de projet et en gestion de la relation client.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellentes capacités d&#39;organisation et de gestion du temps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Capacité à travailler de manière autonome et en équipe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellentes compétences en communication et en résolution de problèmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;text vacancy-description text-align-left &quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Si vous répondez à ces critères et êtes prêt à apporter votre expertise dans un environnement dynamique et stimulant, nous vous encourageons à postuler.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role in Our Story:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;ACT Group is the world’s leading provider of market-based sustainability solutions. Working at the center of the global energy transition, ACT Group helps organizations hit their climate action targets, no matter how ambitious. Since 2009, ACT has become a trusted brand in high-impact climate projects, renewable energy markets, energy efficiency, renewable fuels, and carbon credits. ACT delivers tailor-made solutions from offices in Europe, America and Asia, enabling its partners to join the environmental revolution and pursue more sustainable futures.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:false,&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559738&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559739&amp;quot;:160}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Since our founding in 2009, we have expanded to have offices in Amsterdam, New York, Paris,&amp;nbsp;London,&amp;nbsp;Shanghai,&amp;nbsp;Tokyo&amp;nbsp;and Singapore.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{&amp;quot;134233117&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;134233118&amp;quot;:true,&amp;quot;201341983&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559740&amp;quot;:240}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Commercial Director / Country Manager for the China market, you will play a pivotal role in driving ACT’s sales and market positioning in China. This role combines hands-on commercial leadership with a focus on revenue generation, key client acquisition, and strategic market development. You will be accountable for building a strong commercial pipeline, closing strategic deals, and strengthening ACT’s presence with state-owned enterprises (SOEs), large private enterprises, and strategic partners across China.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will act as the senior commercial face of ACT in China, working closely with APAC leadership and global stakeholders to align China strategy with group priorities, while navigating China’s unique regulatory, policy, and enterprise environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;You will&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and execute ACT’s China commercial front, driving revenue growth, pipeline development, and market expansion in line with APAC and Group objectives. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary senior representative of ACT in China, building credibility and long-term relationships with SOEs, large enterprises, developers, utilities, and strategic partners.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Originate, manage, and close key strategic accounts, with direct ownership of sales KPIs, revenue targets, and major client relationships. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and capitalize on opportunities in China, including partnerships, structured transactions, and long-term framework agreements within the sustainability, energy, and environmental markets. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with internal stakeholders across sales, technical, policy, legal, and operations teams in a matrix structure to deliver commercially viable and compliant solutions. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide commercial input into pricing strategies, deal structures, and contract negotiations, particularly for PPAs and other complex energy or sustainability transactions. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and Develop and continue to build a high-performing commercial team in China, fostering a results-driven culture with clear accountability and continuous improvement. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and develop relationships with internal and external stakeholders, including APAC leadership, HQ functions, regulators, industry bodies, and partners. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Depending on business maturity, ove

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comptable – Contrat VIE (H/F) – Madrid&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vos missions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dans le cadre d&#39;un Volontariat International en Entreprise (VIE), nous recherchons un(e) Comptable pour rejoindre notre équipe Finance. Le poste est basé dans nos locaux de Madrid, avec des interactions quotidiennes avec notre siège social d&#39;Amsterdam et les différentes équipes du Groupe ACT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;En intégrant une entreprise en forte croissance, vous contribuerez activement à l&#39;optimisation de nos processus comptables et financiers. Nous recherchons une personne curieuse, proactive et désireuse d&#39;apprendre, capable de proposer des améliorations et d&#39;accompagner leur mise en œuvre dans un environnement international.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vous serez responsable de la gestion des comptes clients et fournisseurs, depuis le traitement des factures jusqu&#39;aux rapprochements et au reporting financier. Vous travaillerez en étroite collaboration avec le Directeur Général, les équipes Finance, Front Office, Opérations et Trésorerie, ainsi qu&#39;avec nos clients lorsque cela sera nécessaire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;À ce titre, vos principales responsabilités seront :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assurer l&#39;enregistrement et le traitement des factures clients et fournisseurs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Veiller à la bonne application des règles de TVA en collaboration avec les équipes Opérations et Front Office.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Préparer les déclarations mensuelles de TVA dans le respect des échéances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contrôler le circuit d&#39;approbation des factures et assurer le suivi auprès des différents valideurs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Traiter les règlements clients et fournisseurs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Réaliser les rapprochements bancaires et assurer la saisie des relevés bancaires.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gérer le processus de facturation, de rapprochement et de règlement des opérations interentreprises conformément aux accords de services (SLA) du Groupe ACT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Réconcilier les positions interentreprises.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborer avec l&#39;équipe Trésorerie Groupe afin de garantir un niveau de liquidité adapté.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Être l&#39;interlocuteur privilégié pour les questions relatives à la comptabilité.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gérer les appels, courriers et e-mails adressés au service comptable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Préparer les reportings relatifs aux comptes clients et fournisseurs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participer aux travaux de clôture et assister les auditeurs financiers lors des audits.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qui êtes-vous ?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vous êtes diplômé(e) d&#39;une formation de niveau Bac +2 à Bac +3 en comptabilité, gestion ou finance (BTS Comptabilité et Gestion, BUT GEA, DCG ou équivalent).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vous justifiez d&#39;une première expérience en comptabilité (stage, alternance ou premier emploi), idéalement en comptabilité clients et fournisseurs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vous maîtrisez les principes de la comptabilité française. Une connaissance des règles de TVA est un atout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vous parlez couramment le français et maîtrisez l&#39;espagnol à l&#39;oral comme à l&#39;écrit afin d&#39;évoluer efficacement au sein de notre bureau de Madrid.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vous disposez également d&#39;un très bon niveau d&#39;anglais, indispensable pour collaborer avec nos équipes internationales, notamment notre siège d&#39;Amsterdam.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Une première expérience sur Microsoft Dynamics NAV (Navision) ou un autre ERP comptable constitue un plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vous êtes organisé(e), rigoureux(se) et accordez une grande importance à la qualité et à la fiabilité de votre travail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vous faites preuve d&#39;autonomie, de curiosité et d&#39;un véritable esprit d&

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role in Our Story:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ACT is the world’s leading provider of market-based sustainability solutions. As enablers of the global energy transition, we help organizations hit their climate targets and maximize their profits while reducing risk. Since 2009, we have become a trusted brand in climate projects, green electricity markets, renewable energies and energy efficiency, renewable fuels, emission allowances, and carbon credits. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From our offices in Amsterdam, New York, Singapore, Shanghai, and Paris, we draw on over a decade of market knowledge to deliver tailor-made solutions and sterling service. Business Development Associates work in region-specific teams to create product portfolios for clients that meet their specific needs and help them drive climate action their way. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that this is not an active job opening, but an opportunity for us to connect with potential talent as we plan for future roles.&amp;nbsp;If you would prefer to interview only for positions that are currently open, we kindly encourage you to wait until a suitable active role becomes available and aligns with your career goals.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In essence, your role involves&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Corporate Sales Manager will be responsible for identifying, structuring, and closing high-value deals that align with ACT Group’s strategic objectives. This role requires a deep understanding of the sustainability landscape, a strong network of industry contacts, and a proven track record of successful deal origination in RECs, carbon credits, biomethane. The ideal candidate will be a strategic thinker with excellent negotiation skills and the ability to build lasting relationships with key stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deal Origination&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and originate new business opportunities that align with ACT Group’s strategic goals and market focus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain a strong pipeline of high-quality deals across targeted markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct thorough market research and analysis to identify trends, opportunities, and potential risks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client Relationship Management&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and nurture relationships with key clients, partners, and industry stakeholders to drive business development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand clients’ needs and develop tailored solutions that meet their objectives while aligning with ACT Group’s capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary point of contact for clients throughout the deal lifecycle, ensuring a high level of client satisfaction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deal Structuring and Negotiation&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the structuring, negotiation, and execution of complex deals, ensuring they are commercially viable and strategically aligned with company goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal teams, including legal, finance, operations, and R&amp;amp;D, to ensure seamless deal execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Present and defend deal proposals to senior management and the Board, providing clear rationale and expected outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Intelligence and Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay informed about market developments, regulatory changes, and competitor activities that could impact the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic insights and recommendations to senior management based on market analysis and industry trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development of

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role in Our Story:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;PDq2pG_selectionAnchorContainer&quot; data-start=&quot;28&quot; data-end=&quot;341&quot;&gt;As our Global Brand &amp;amp; Communications Manager, you will shape how ACT is seen, understood and experienced around the world. Reporting to the Global Director of Marketing, you will lead the global Brand &amp;amp; Communications function, manage a team of six and work closely with Executive Leadership and Commercial teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;343&quot; data-end=&quot;787&quot;&gt;ACT is evolving from a global leader in environmental commodities into a broader sustainability solutions provider. At this defining stage in our growth, you will help strengthen our market position, increase ACT’s visibility and build a trusted, differentiated brand. You will work with talented colleagues across Europe, the Americas and Asia-Pacific to help organisations accelerate the transition from climate ambition to measurable action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In essence, your role involves:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1195&quot; data-end=&quot;2134&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1qjsj6r&quot; data-start=&quot;1195&quot; data-end=&quot;1300&quot;&gt;Own and evolve ACT’s global brand and communications strategy in line with our business transformation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;6zowa0&quot; data-start=&quot;1301&quot; data-end=&quot;1394&quot;&gt;Develop clear messaging and compelling storytelling that strengthens ACT’s market position.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1o2u6jq&quot; data-start=&quot;1395&quot; data-end=&quot;1480&quot;&gt;Translate business priorities into relevant, credible and impactful communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1pmijs1&quot; data-start=&quot;1481&quot; data-end=&quot;1560&quot;&gt;Lead, coach and develop a high-performing Brand &amp;amp; Communications team of six.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1udd1ci&quot; data-start=&quot;1561&quot; data-end=&quot;1673&quot;&gt;Ensure a consistent brand experience across campaigns, content, digital channels and corporate communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;171wig8&quot; data-start=&quot;1674&quot; data-end=&quot;1787&quot;&gt;Increase visibility and engagement across the website, social media, search and AI-powered discovery platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1osz7zm&quot; data-start=&quot;1788&quot; data-end=&quot;1934&quot;&gt;Use market insights and performance data to continuously improve brand, content, campaigns, digital performance and communication effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;ycv6hv&quot; data-start=&quot;1935&quot; data-end=&quot;2028&quot;&gt;Partner with senior stakeholders to turn business priorities into impactful communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1b0cq1c&quot; data-start=&quot;2029&quot; data-end=&quot;2134&quot;&gt;Manage external agencies and champion AI to improve marketing effectiveness and operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;2136&quot; data-end=&quot;2405&quot;&gt;Success in this role means strengthening ACT’s global brand, increasing visibility and engagement, improving digital performance, embedding AI within the Brand &amp;amp; Communications function and building a high-performing team that contributes directly to commercial growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Expertise:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You combine strategic thinking with hands-on leadership and know how to translate business strategy into clear messaging, compelling market stories and consistent brand experiences. You are able to deliver impactful communications and measurable business results, with a strong focus on commercial growth.&lt;/p&gt;
