&lt;h1 data-start=&quot;2696&quot; data-end=&quot;2715&quot;&gt;Lo Que Aprenderás&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;2717&quot; data-end=&quot;2768&q

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role in Our Story:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time role for an experienced manager in clean energy regulation, responsible for ensuring that ACT can develop innovative new market-based products, suitable for the region, that enable end-to-end, sustainable decarbonization. Reporting to the Global Director, R&amp;amp;D and Sustainability. The role is based in Amsterdam, and requires occasional travel, both within Europe and to other destinations. In essence, your role involves:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and deliver a complex portfolio of innovative products for EMEA that is informed by regional and national regulatory developments and sustainability standards and guidance. The emphasis is on Europe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and develop of a team of experts in regulation and environmental product development that is focused on the EMEA region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and share regulatory intelligence and deep technical understanding of supply/demand fundamentals of carbon and renewable energy markets with internal and external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate transactions, support commercial teams, and provide input into industry and regulatory processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate globally on product development with other regional R&amp;amp;D teams, and other teams within ACT as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent ACT at eg, trade association meetings, exhibitions, and conferences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Expertise, Our Shared Success:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in this role, we are looking for candidates with the following qualifications and attributes:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years’ work experience that provides a deep understanding of clean energy regulation markets in the region – renewable energy, fuels, and carbon markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High commercial acumen with a strong track record of using regulations to inform the development of new products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to develop, motivate, and nurture a talented team of specialists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A commercial and creative mindset, strong collaboration skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English is expected; additional fluency in French, German, or Italian is helpful.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;University educated, ideally with post-graduate qualification having a strong analytical component&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you meet these criteria and are ready to contribute your expertise to a dynamic and challenging environment, we encourage you to apply.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role in Our Story:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In essence, your role involves:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with a range of clients across various industries, each with their own set of exciting challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, manage, and grow your own portfolio of clients using strong interpersonal and stellar communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Find your own leads through cold calling, driven by your love for challenges and career growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Break down barriers and go the extra mile daily to keep your clients engaged and satisfied&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embrace teamwork, fitting into a team approach that emphasizes working together to succeed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rely on your team for support and leverage their unique skills to close deals collaboratively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benefit clients through a collaborative work style where most deals involve two or more traders, offering combined expertise, skills, and networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Expertise:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in this role, we are looking for candidates with the following qualifications and attributes:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Young and ambitious professional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferably some experience or at least an affinity with finance and sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cold-calling pro and charismatic portfolio manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepreneurial spirit, energetic, ambitious and curious&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated and persistent, even in tough situations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eager to learn and welcome constructive criticism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Not afraid to fail and try again&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;***This is not a job rotation schedule, but an open application for a Sales Trader role, as all our Sales Traders benefit from the Graduate Program training.***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role in Our Story:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In essence, your role involves&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading and managing the trading of biomethane quotas, ensuring compliance with all regulatory standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building and maintaining strong relationships with suppliers, customers, and regulatory bodies to expand our impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing expert insights and staying ahead of legal and market developments related to biomethane quotas and renewable energy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maximizing revenue from biomethane trading by leveraging our existing network and spotting new market opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting the registration process with environmental authorities, facilitating seamless trading transactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating closely with the trading team, aligning on strategy, and sharing valuable market intelligence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
