&lt;li&gt;A Bachelor’s/Master&#39;s, preferably in Business, Economics, or Finance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-3 years’ experience in emissions trading, renewable energy certificates, or related environmental commodities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willing to learn about and develop a niche industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Persistent, Ambitious and Energetic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the Fuel Quality Directive (FQD) and biomethane quota regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional analytical skills and comfort with complex regulatory details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and negotiation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and as a collaborative team member.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in gas or biomethane trading would be a strong advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

